snippet.textDisplay: The lines coming out from the tires is a TPMS system. If you look on the controller mounted under the heater controls you will see options for sand, snow, mud and crosscountry/highway driving. It adjust tire pressure with the inboard compressor based off the terrain you are on or select. The horn will only work with the headlights on. There is a blackout mode which will shine a light roughly 5ft in front of the truck while driving at night to prevent being seen. Also the electrical system is NOT a 12v system, it is a 24v.

snippet.textDisplay: A M16 is a fully automatic rifle that is basically the standard issue rifle our military issues to our service men. The AR-15 is a similar variant of the M16. It's a civilian model basically.  No you cannot buy an M16. Well you can but they do have a mandatory minimum if you are caught with one. Lol. You can' get a federal license that allows you to have one. Probably about the average cost of one. Is $16,000. The M16 shoots a 5.56 mm bullet, or a 223 if you will. They have a lot of kinetic energy. A simple way to show people the difference between the kinetic energy of a M16 compared to an AK-47, is to take two one gallon milk jugs and fill them with water. And shoot one with the AK-47. And one with of course the M16. well you can't shoot the M16 so we'll just substitute an AR-15. The AK will make a perfect hole through the milk jug and the water will leak out through the hole. Whereas the AR-15 the milk jug will explode. I mean I've read where people that have been say hit in the lower leg, the bullet ends up exiting through the neck. The bullet just bounces around inside the body. I know kind of a morbid description, just throw some facts out there.
